Package com.millicast

Interface Client.Listener

All Known Subinterfaces:
Publisher.Listener, Subscriber.Listener
Enclosing class:
Client
public static interface Client.Listener
The Client Listener struct which contains methods that will be called on specific events from a Client object.

  • Method Details

    • onConnected

      void onConnected()
      Called when the WebSocket connection to Millicast is opened

    • onDisconnected

      void onDisconnected()
      Called when the WebSocket connection to Millicast is closed. If this was an unintended disconnect, a reconnect attempt will happen automatically by default. To turn off the automatic reconnect, set Client.Option.autoReconnect to false.

    • onConnectionError

      void onConnectionError(int status, String reason)
      Called when the attempt to connect to Millicast failed.
      Parameters:
      status - The HTTP status code, if available. Otherwise, -1.
      reason - The reason the connection attempt failed.

    • onSignalingError

      void onSignalingError(String reason)
      Called when millicast sends back an error message in response to a websocket command
      Parameters:
      reason - The error message received from millicast

    • onStatsReport

      void onStatsReport(org.webrtc.RTCStatsReport report)
      Called when a new rtc stats report has been collected. Note that you must enable the stats to be able to receive a report.

    • onViewerCount

      void onViewerCount(int count)
      Called when a new viewer join the stream or when a viewer quit the stream
      Parameters:
      count - The current number of viewers.
